1.2 0-1.2.6z"></path></svg></div></div></div></a></div><div class="x1lliihq x1n2onr6 xh8yej3 x4gyw5p x14z9mp xhe4ym4 xaudc5v x1j53mea"><a class="x1i10hfl xjbqb8w x1ejq31n x18oe1m7 x1sy0etr xstzfhl x972fbf x10w94by x1qhh985 x14e42zd x9f619 x1ypdohk xt0psk2 x3ct3a4 xdj266r x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x16tdsg8 x1hl2dhg xggy1nq x1a2a7pz _a6hd" href="/atelierjolieofficial/p/DW4NgywgNgj/" role="link" tabindex="0"><div class="_aagu"><div style="padding-bottom:133.33333333333331%" class="_aagv"><img alt="Atelier Jolie welcomes a new Artist in Residence this spring, Ghanaian-British artist @AkwasiBrenyaMensa. 

Centred on gathering as method, Brenya-Mensa creates sensory environments through space, sound, memory, image and food. Most recently known for his Pan-African dining concept @tataleworld, his practice explores public convening as a structured mode of inquiry and exchange through the ritual of dining together. The first floor becomes a working site for experimentation and collaboration in dialogue with Atelier Jolie’s mission.

Public programming will begin April 2026. Link in bio.

Photos by @argenisphoto

